@startuml
title Viaverse Business Account / Merchant Ops — Component Diagram

component "KMP / Business UI\nprofile\ncatalog\nleads\ninsights" as Client
component "API Gateway / BFF\nBusiness API facade" as BFF
component "BusinessController\nCatalogController\nStaffController" as Controller
component "Business Use Cases\nCreateBusiness\nVerifyBusiness\nManageCatalog\nManageStaff\nPublishBusiness" as UseCases
component "Business Policies\nowner/staff permissions\npublish-ready\nregional verification\nsubscription gates" as Policies
component "Ports\nBusinessRepo\nIdentityPort\nMediaPort\nBillingPort\nSearchPort\nOutboxPort" as Ports
component "identity-service\naccount capability\nstaff users\nroles" as Identity
component "media-service\nlogo/photos\ngallery moderation" as Media
component "billing-service\ntrial/plan\ninvoice/payment state" as Billing
database "PostgreSQL\nbusiness\nbranch\ncatalog\nstaff_role" as DB
component "search/trust\npublic projection\nranking signals" as Search
queue "Kafka / Outbox\nBusinessCreated\nCatalogUpdated\nBusinessPublished" as Kafka

Client --> BFF : HTTPS
BFF --> Controller : REST
Controller --> UseCases : command/query
UseCases --> Policies : validate
Policies --> Ports : ports
Ports --> Identity : capability/staff
Ports --> Media : media refs
Ports --> Billing : subscription gates
Ports --> DB : persist
Ports --> Search : publish projection
UseCases --> Kafka : events

note bottom
Business UI may be one app flow today and a separate store app later.
The backend business bounded context should not depend on that client packaging choice.
end note
@enduml
